text.section:
The plan of reorganization shall be submitted to the Commissioner for approval at least 60 days before the effective date of the reorganization, together with:
the proposed articles of incorporation and bylaws of the mutual insurance holding company;
the amendments to the articles of incorporation and bylaws of the mutual insurer to reorganize as a stock insurer;
a 5-year plan of operation for the mutual insurance holding company and the reorganized stock insurer, including any plans for:
an initial public offering of stock in the reorganized stock insurer; or
the transfer of assets or liabilities from the reorganized stock insurer or any subsidiaries of the reorganized stock insurer to the mutual insurance holding company;
a list of the officers and directors of the mutual insurance holding company and the reorganized stock insurer;
a biography of each officer and director of the mutual insurance holding company and the reorganized stock insurer; and
any other documents or information requested by the Commissioner.
